    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My notes for this feature.\n\nWe need the compression to happen in the context of the thread requesting things.\n\nThis means:\n- on the write path, we should compress in the `grpc_call_start_batch` call tree\n- on the read path, we should decompress in the `grpc_completion_queue_next` call tree\n\nOne idea to do this cleanly (my preferred currently):\n- `grpc_byte_buffer_type` picks up a `GRPC_BB_COMPRESSED_SLICE_BUFFER` type\n- `grpc_call_start_batch` passes these buffer types through when it sees them, and tries to compress based upon channel configuration if not\n- `grpc_byte_buffer_reader` learns to decompress\n\nPlease make `grpc_byte_buffer_reader` stack allocated (change `grpc_byte_buffer_reader_create` to `grpc_byte_buffer_init` as part of this work).\n\nThe `grpc_call_start_batch` API will need a bit when writing indicating that a particular message is _NOT_ to be compressed. This is a security requirement to prevent CRIME/BEAST style attacks.\n\nWe will want a channel level option to enable/disable compression.\n\n`grpc_begin_message` will need a bit to specify compressed or not. `stream_encoder.c` will need to be updated to interpret it. `frame_data.c` and `grpc_sopb_add_begin_message` will need to act upon this bit. Probably `http_client_filter.c` will also need to act upon this bit.\n"
